#3.Which store/s has a good quarterly growth rate in Q3’2012
# Here we will first convert the Date to datetime datatype first

# Then we will add the variable date_qtr because we want to divide the divide the dates
# quartely for example 2010Q1,2010Q2,2010Q3,2010Q4,2011Q1,2011Q2....and so fourth.

# We then add another variable year just to find the year of the date.
#Then we add another variable quarter to find the quarter of the date for example First
# quarter,2nd Quarter,and so on....

walmart_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(walmart_data['Date'])
In [279]:
# date_qtr variable being added
walmart_data['date_qtr'] = pd.to_datetime(walmart_data['Date']).dt.to_period('Q')
In [280]:
# a year variable being added
walmart_data['year'] = walmart_data['Date'].dt.year
In [281]:
# a quarter variable being added
walmart_data['quarter'] = walmart_data['Date'].dt.quarter

# Because we want to find a Store with good quartely growth rate,what we are required to do is to calculate

# the percentage change from 2010 to 2011,from 2011 to 2012

#4.Some holidays have a negative impact on sales.
